    words = input().strip()

def reverse_2(words:str)->str:
    
    a = len(words)
    stk = []
    ans = ''

    i = 0
    while i<a:

        if words[i].isalnum():
            stk.append(words[i])
            i+=1

        elif words[i] is ' ':
            while stk:
                ans+=stk.pop()
            ans+=' '
            i+=1

        elif words[i] is '<':
            while stk:
                ans+=stk.pop()

            while words[i] is not '>':
                ans+=words[i]
                i+=1
            ans+='>'
            i+=1
    while stk:
        ans+=stk.pop()
    return ans.strip()

print(reverse_2(words))
